<h1>Incremental Specification</h1>
</center>

<h3>
(b) Two I-cards are consisitent if the super-components
in the overlapped sub-nets of the corresponding C-cards are identical.

<p>
(c) Two C-cards are connected if they have overlapped
sub-nets.
The C-cards can be integrated if there exists
a path between any two C-cards, i.e., they are all connected.

<p>
A collection of cards can be integrated if 
conditions (a), (b) and (c) hold for any two cards.

<p>
